04/05/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The leader of the main opposition Democratic Party (DP), Sali Berisha, said Tuesday (3 May) that the reshuffle of the DP chairmanship was needed to rejuvenate the party before the 3 July parliamentary elections. The DP National Council voted Monday on a new chairmanship, which includes some longtime associates of Berisha.
In other news Tuesday, the finance ministry announced that Germany has agreed to provide 16.7m euros in loans to help Albania revamp the water supply systems of two towns, Pogradec and Korca. Germany has so far contributed 326m euros to Albania's development. (Albanian News - 04/05/05; AP - 03/05/05)
